        "\t\t\t\t\t\t23. Why is the Venus of Willendorf considered 'too small and ugly'?\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tA.It does not meet modern standards of beauty.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tB.It is made of inferior materials.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tC.It lacks the idealized proportions of classical sculptures.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tD.It is an abstract and unconventional representation.",
        "\t\t\t\t\t\t24. What is the significance of the Venus of Willendorf's exaggerated features?\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tA.They reflect the artist's personal preferences.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tB.They represent the artist's skill in realistic portraiture.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tC.They are symbolic of fertility and the different stages of a woman's life.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tD.They were intended to be humorous or grotesque.",
        "\t\t\t\t\t\t25. The text describes Aphrodite as:\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tA.A goddess of war and conflict\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tB.The first lifelike statue that shows the female figure in three dimensions\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tC.A goddess of the harvest and fertility\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tD.A goddess of wisdom and justice",
