            "\t\t\t\t\t\t20. How can you prevent a function from modifying an argument passed to it?\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tA. const keyword\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tB. static keyword\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tC. volatile keyword\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tD. mutable keyword",
            "\t\t\t\t\t\t21. Which operator is used for dynamic memory deallocation in C++?\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tA. delete\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tB. remove\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tC. free\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tD. deallocate",
            "\t\t\t\t\t\t22. What is the correct way to comment a single line in C++?\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tA. /* This is a comment */\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tB. // This is a comment\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tC. # This is a comment\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tD. -- This is a comment",
            "\t\t\t\t\t\t23. What does endl do in C++?\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tA. Ends the program\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tB. Inserts a newline character\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tC. Erases the previous line\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tD. None of the above",
            "\t\t\t\t\t\t24. Which concept allows multiple functions to have the same name but different parameters?\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tA. Function overloading\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tB. Function overriding\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tC. Function hiding\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tD. Function nesting",
            "\t\t\t\t\t\t25. Which C++ access specifier makes class members accessible only within the class itself?\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tA. public\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tB. private\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tC. protected\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tD. global"
        };
        char correctAnswers[NUM_QUESTIONS] = {'B', 'B', 'A', 'B', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'B', 'B', 'C', 'B', 'B', 'C', 'C', 'A', 'B', 'B', 'D', 'A', 'A', 'B', 'B', 'A', 'B'};
